message.content:
A Brittany spaniel is a medium-sized breed of gun dog with origins in France.
The breed typically weighs between 30–45 pounds and stands about 17–21 inches tall at the shoulder.
Coats are dense, and range in color from liver and white to orange and white, with possible roaning or ticking.
They have long, floppy ears and a tail that is typically docked in the US.
Brittanys are highly energetic and need regular exercise and mental stimulation to stay happy and healthy.
They are versatile hunting dogs, used for pointing, flushing, and retrieving game birds.
Brittanys are also popular as family pets due to their friendly and affectionate nature.
